docs.lead_paragraph: WAYNESBORO, Ga. — Scores of mourners gathered last week at a rural cemetery for a service to mark the first anniversary of the slaying of Ahmaud Arbery, a 25-year-old Black man who was chased by a trio of white men and shot to death on a residential street.

headline.main: Before Breonna Taylor and George Floyd, There Was Ahmaud Arbery
headline.print_headline: A Year Later, Mourning the Killing of a Black Jogger in Georgia

docs.abstract: Firsthand accounts accuse Derek Chauvin, the police officer who pressed his knee into George Floyd’s neck in Minneapolis, of using similar tactics on detainees over the years.
docs.snippet: Firsthand accounts accuse Derek Chauvin, the police officer who pressed his knee into George Floyd’s neck in Minneapolis, of using similar tactics on detainees over the years.
docs.lead_paragraph: Nearly three years before the Minneapolis police officer Derek Chauvin knelt on George Floyd as he cried out that he couldn’t breathe last May, Zoya Code found herself in a similar position: handcuffed facedown on the ground, with Mr. Chauvin’s knee on her.

headline.main: ‘Don’t Kill Me’: Others Tell of Abuse by Officer Who Knelt on George Floyd
headline.print_headline: Floyd Case Fit Pattern of Roughness by Officer Accused in Killing

docs.abstract: The tragedy of racism is only part of the story in two very different plays from London that carry a dimension of meaning not usually seen in this country.
docs.snippet: The tragedy of racism is only part of the story in two very different plays from London that carry a dimension of meaning not usually seen in this country.
docs.lead_paragraph: As far as theater is concerned, the pandemic has been a paradox, shrinking life down to lockdown bubbles and simultaneously expanding horizons. When you can stream plays from Europe as easily as from Brooklyn, the world seems more interconnected than in the past — tied together by bonds of humanity.

headline.main: Making Black Lives, Not Just Black Deaths, Matter Onstage

docs.lead_paragraph: More than 160 Confederate symbols were removed from public spaces or renamed last year after the death of George Floyd, more than the previous four years combined, a watchdog group said on Tuesday.

headline.main: Over 160 Confederate Symbols Were Removed in 2020, Group Says

docs.abstract: Once the Trump mob attacked officers, Republican hypocrisy was exposed.
docs.snippet: Once the Trump mob attacked officers, Republican hypocrisy was exposed.
docs.lead_paragraph: Blue Lives Matter is officially dead. People may continue to chant and post the slogan, but it is dead. Senate Republicans killed it last week when they voted to acquit Donald Trump of inciting an insurrection that left one officer dead and 138 injured. (Two officers who responded to the insurrection later died by suicide.)

docs.abstract: Mr. Barr, then the attorney general, rejected a plea deal days after Mr. Floyd died, worried in part of protesters calling it lenient. Derek Chauvin was set to plead guilty to third-degree murder.

docs.lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS — It was three days after George Floyd died in police custody last May, and businesses in the Twin Cities were on fire. Police officers were shooting rubber bullets and tear gas to hold back protesters, their anger fueled by a cellphone video of Mr. Floyd, a Black man, gasping for breath under the knee of a white officer.

headline.main: Why William Barr Rejected a Plea Deal in the George Floyd Killing
headline.print_headline: City Torn Apart Over Police Shooting Braces for a Trial

docs.abstract: Timothy Loehmann, who was fired from the Cleveland police force after the shooting death of 12-year-old Tamir Rice, has quietly played with a semipro team in Ohio.
docs.snippet: Timothy Loehmann, who was fired from the Cleveland police force after the shooting death of 12-year-old Tamir Rice, has quietly played with a semipro team in Ohio.
docs.lead_paragraph: When the new player appeared on the semipro football team made up of emergency workers, he simply went by Tim or Timmy. He was noticeably bad at football, said Randy Knight, a lineman on the team, who took Tim under his wing and taught him the basics: assuming a three-point stance, “firing off” the line, proper hand placement at the line of scrimmage.

headline.main: Protests Rise After Officer in Tamir Rice Shooting Plays on Football Team
headline.print_headline: Protests Rise After Officer Who Shot Tamir Rice Plays on a Semipro Team in Ohio
